HEADWORD: Tellurism
<hw>Tel"lu*rism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An hypothesis of
animal magnetism propounded by Dr. Keiser, in Germany, in which the
phenomena are ascribed to the agency of a telluric spirit or
influence.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>S. Thompson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tellurite</ent>⟦br⟧
